 studies.<\/p><p>Since its inception in 2002, the program has trained over 1,700 fellows, who now work in more than 140 countries, serving in leadership roles across governments, NGOs, educational institutions, peacekeeping agencies, and international organizations.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><h2>2. Aga Khan Foundation Scholarships for African Students<\/h2><ul><li><strong>Levels:<\/strong> Master\u2019s and PhD<\/li><li><strong>Study Locations:<\/strong> Worldwide<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/the.akdn\/en\/what-we-do\/developing-human-capacity\/education\/international-scholarships\">Official Website<\/a><\/li><\/ul><p>The Aga Khan Foundation\u2019s International Scholarship Program (AKF ISP) offers postgraduate education opportunities to exceptional scholars from selected countries who lack other means of funding their studies.<\/p><p>Since its establishment in 1969, the program has supported over 1,000 students. Award recipients are chosen through a global, annual, and competitive application process, with a limited number of new awards granted each cycle.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><h2>3. MasterCard Foundation Scholarships<\/h2><ul><li><strong>Levels:<\/strong> Master\u2019s and PhD<\/li><li><strong>Study Locations:<\/strong> The US and Africa<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/mastercardfdn.org\/all\/scholars\/\">Official Website<\/a><\/li><\/ul><p>The Mastercard Foundation Scholars Program aims to develop the next generation of transformative leaders by providing highly talented, service-oriented young people, primarily from Africa, with the opportunity to pursue higher education and improve their leadership potential.<\/p><p>Collaborating with educational institutions, NGOs, and the Mastercard Foundation Scholars community, the program ensures that young people receive inclusive and relevant education, transition into dignified work, and lead impactful lives.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><h2>4. Fulbright Foreign Student Program<\/h2><ul><li><strong>Level:<\/strong> Master\u2019s<\/li><li><strong>Study Location<\/strong>: The US<\/li><li><a href=\"http:\/\/exchanges.state.gov\/non-us\/program\/fulbright-foreign-student-program\">Official Website<\/a><\/li><\/ul><p>The Fulbright Foreign Student Program provides an opportunity for graduate students, young professionals, and artists from abroad to research and study in the United States for six months to one year at U.S. universities.<\/p><p>This program accepts public applications and is open to individuals who have completed their undergraduate education and hold a degree equivalent to a bachelor&#8217;s degree.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><h2>5. MSFS Full-Tuition Scholarships for African Students<\/h2><ul><li><strong>Level:<\/strong> Master\u2019s<\/li><li><strong>Study Location:<\/strong> The US<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/msfs.georgetown.edu\/msfs-continues-Africa-scholarship\">Official Website<\/a><\/li><\/ul><p>These are grants for Africans from Sub-Saharan Africa to study in the US in the Master of Science in Foreign Service (MSFS) program at Georgetown University in Washington DC.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p><h2>6. The Ibrahim Scholarships<\/h2><ul><li><strong>Levels:<\/strong> Master\u2019s and PHD<\/li><li><strong>Study Location:<\/strong> The UK<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/mo.ibrahim.foundation\/scholarships\">Official Website<\/a><\/li><\/ul><p>The Ibrahim Scholarship provides African students with Master&#8217;s degrees and PhD scholarships for aspiring them to study in the UK at London Business School, SOAS, or the University of Birmingham.<\/p><p>if you want to know about <a href=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/types-of-scholarships-in-canada\/\">types of scholarships in Canada<\/a> read this article:<\/p><p><blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"cIHMsQHQom\"><a href=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/types-of-scholarships-in-canada\/\">7 Types of Scholarships in Canada for International Students<\/a><\/blockquote><iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restrict